During the [[:en:Edo period|Edo period]], successive shoguns granted the shrine a seal and a stipend of ten koku. In [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 14 (1881), it was designated as a {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|ja|県社|lt=Ken-sha|1=Modern_system_of_ranked_Shinto_shrines#Metropolitan_and_Prefectural_Shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prefectural Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度}}.<ref name="jinjacho"/> The current structure dates to [[:en:Enkyō (Edo period)|Enkyō]] 4 (1747).<ref name="jinjacho"/>
